WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:00.020 --> 00:00:01.230
Clank. clank. clank.

2
00:00:01.450 --> 00:00:04.160
They say three things
are buried in mines:

3
00:00:04.760 --> 00:00:05.730
ore.

4
00:00:06.020 --> 00:00:06.720
money.

5
00:00:06.910 --> 00:00:08.380
and people.

6
00:00:09.310 --> 00:00:11.650
On a grave covered in coal ash.

7
00:00:11.900 --> 00:00:14.160
a dazzling paradise rises above ground.

8
00:00:15.040 --> 00:00:18.160
Its shiny lights are so blinding

9
00:00:18.860 --> 00:00:22.670
that no one looks down at their feet.

10
00:00:24.620 --> 00:00:25.310
[Prosecutor Ju Taeseon]

11
00:00:25.310 --> 00:00:28.250
Just when I thought everything was over.

12
00:00:30.030 --> 00:00:31.830
he made me a proposal.

13
00:00:33.950 --> 00:00:35.100
A proposal...

14
00:00:35.420 --> 00:00:36.650
I couldn't refuse.

15
00:00:36.780 --> 00:00:39.410
Prosecutor Ju. I respect you...

16
00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:47.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

17
00:00:59.050 --> 00:01:01.220
[Park Siwoo]

18
00:01:03.670 --> 00:01:06.850
[Kim Yunsik]

19
00:01:11.420 --> 00:01:13.960
[Kwak Seunghwan:
because of property division?]

20
00:01:13.960 --> 00:01:15.670
[Kim (Koryoin): drug overdose]

21
00:01:15.670 --> 00:01:17.510
[Found in a small room
on the second floor]

22
00:01:17.510 --> 00:01:20.360
[Last abandoned mine in Danhyeon
has been converted into a casino...]

23
00:01:20.360 --> 00:01:22.460
[Danhyeon Land construction led by Ohsong:
casino. hotel. theme park. resort...]

24
00:01:22.460 --> 00:01:24.640
[First female executive
in the casino industry...]

25
00:01:24.640 --> 00:01:26.920
[Promises "transparent management
and regional win-win"]

26
00:01:26.920 --> 00:01:30.980
[Danhyeon City "Casino Owner Murdered";
the suspect is his driver. Lee]

27
00:01:35.110 --> 00:01:37.500
[The Prosecutor's Proposal]

28
00:01:49.350 --> 00:01:51.180
[Prosecution]

29
00:01:55.450 --> 00:01:58.000
Who the hell is Lee Chaeha? Get out here!

30
00:02:01.110 --> 00:02:02.190
I am.

31
00:02:15.490 --> 00:02:16.610
Go on.

32
00:02:17.320 --> 00:02:18.260
Pick them up.

33
00:02:37.230 --> 00:02:40.140
[Fine Collection Division]

34
00:02:56.440 --> 00:02:59.200
Call me early in the morning

35
00:02:59.350 --> 00:03:07.370
making a fuss over this petty cash again.
and I'll...

36
00:03:12.610 --> 00:03:13.650
Look at me.

37
00:03:19.829 --> 00:03:22.200
Getting rid of you is a piece of cake.

38
00:03:27.200 --> 00:03:29.500
-Director Park!
-Yes.

39
00:03:29.770 --> 00:03:31.850
Keep your men in line.

40
00:03:37.079 --> 00:03:38.980
-Goodbye.
-Yeah!

41
00:03:45.060 --> 00:03:48.140
She thinks she's all that just because
her father owns Ohsong Group.

42
00:03:48.140 --> 00:03:50.070
So what if she's a casino director?

43
00:03:50.700 --> 00:03:52.650
Rich people are the worst.

44
00:03:53.400 --> 00:03:56.010
No one's fault but hers
for not paying her fines on time.

45
00:03:56.010 --> 00:03:56.970
Right?

46
00:03:58.370 --> 00:04:00.030
Let's get promoted to Grade 7 ASAP

47
00:04:00.030 --> 00:04:02.370
and escape
this damn fine collection division.

48
00:04:02.370 --> 00:04:05.500
Or stick it out
and become a prosecutor's investigator.

49
00:04:06.340 --> 00:04:07.380
Thank you.

50
00:04:09.130 --> 00:04:10.930
Don't you agree. Director Park?

51
00:04:12.120 --> 00:04:13.740
Let's go for lunch.

52
00:04:34.210 --> 00:04:35.810
You're on duty today. right?

53
00:04:37.520 --> 00:04:40.670
[Public Official ID: Ju Taeseon.
Supreme Prosecutors' Office]

54
00:04:40.670 --> 00:04:42.800
Yes. for post-mortem investigation.

55
00:04:43.130 --> 00:04:44.200
See you later.

56
00:04:44.450 --> 00:04:46.110
Senior Assistant Lee Chaeha.

57
00:04:49.030 --> 00:04:51.190
[Public Official ID: Lee Chaeha.
Supreme Prosecutors' Office]

58
00:04:51.190 --> 00:04:52.180
Chaeha.

59
00:04:52.409 --> 00:04:53.210
Ah. yes.

60
00:04:53.420 --> 00:04:54.180
Come on.

61
00:05:00.790 --> 00:05:02.980
Are you on duty with Prosecutor Ju today?

62
00:05:02.980 --> 00:05:05.480
No. I'm not.

63
00:05:06.410 --> 00:05:08.690
Psy-cho-path.

64
00:05:08.970 --> 00:05:09.840
What?

65
00:05:10.420 --> 00:05:11.830
Prosecutor Ju.

66
00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:14.040
I don't know if he's human
or just a handsome mannequin.

67
00:05:14.040 --> 00:05:15.860
Always has a poker face.

68
00:05:16.320 --> 00:05:18.490
Doesn't smile. cry. or get mad.

69
00:05:18.610 --> 00:05:21.670
And you can't mention or ask about
his personal life.

70
00:05:22.130 --> 00:05:23.820
He's way too aloof.

71
00:05:25.080 --> 00:05:27.490
But he's good at his job.
Isn't that all that matters?

72
00:05:27.490 --> 00:05:29.810
Oh. please.
He meddles in all sorts of cases.

73
00:05:29.810 --> 00:05:31.740
squeezing his investigators dry.

74
00:05:32.290 --> 00:05:34.530
[Prosecution]

75
00:05:35.900 --> 00:05:38.850
Pursuing justice isn't easy.

76
00:05:38.970 --> 00:05:42.230
Having too strong a sense of justice
is just self-serving.

77
00:05:43.170 --> 00:05:45.260
You know about
Prosecutor Yoon Soyeon's suicide. right?

78
00:05:45.260 --> 00:05:47.650
Because he blew the whistle.
not only was he demoted.

79
00:05:47.650 --> 00:05:49.980
but even his chief
was forced to step down.

80
00:05:51.260 --> 00:05:52.970
He just did what had to be done.

81
00:05:54.040 --> 00:05:56.270
Things that no one else could do.

82
00:05:58.190 --> 00:05:59.159
Huh?

83
00:06:00.070 --> 00:06:01.160
Chaeha.

84
00:06:01.330 --> 00:06:02.870
are you close with Prosecutor Ju?

85
00:06:02.870 --> 00:06:03.750
What?

86
00:06:04.140 --> 00:06:05.690
No. I'm not.

87
00:06:07.710 --> 00:06:09.390
I just respect him.

88
00:06:09.990 --> 00:06:12.000
Anyway. why else would
an investigator of his

89
00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:13.990
go abroad for study at this time?

90
00:06:14.860 --> 00:06:18.170
I wonder who will take that empty spot.

91
00:06:19.230 --> 00:06:21.810
Definitely not us.
since we have the least seniority.

92
00:06:21.810 --> 00:06:22.940
Aren't you envious?

93
00:06:24.570 --> 00:06:25.770
Come to think of it.

94
00:06:26.470 --> 00:06:30.190
I'm more afraid of fine defaulters
than Prosecutor Ju.

95
00:07:18.730 --> 00:07:19.870
See you later.

96
00:07:20.180 --> 00:07:21.840
Senior Assistant Lee Chaeha.

97
00:07:30.760 --> 00:07:31.510
Huh?

98
00:07:31.930 --> 00:07:34.650
[Notice of Change in On-Duty Prosecutor:
Lee Jeonggeun -> Ju Taeseon]

99
00:07:33.190 --> 00:07:34.310
Ju Taeseon?

100
00:07:35.760 --> 00:07:37.920
Damn it. When did they change it?

101
00:07:38.659 --> 00:07:41.120
Psy-cho-path.

102
00:07:42.090 --> 00:07:44.040
Psychopath...

103
00:08:46.920 --> 00:08:47.920
Hello?

104
00:08:48.460 --> 00:08:50.010
A body was found.

105
00:08:58.040 --> 00:09:01.060
Oh my. what on earth happened?

106
00:09:01.070 --> 00:09:03.120
They went in ages ago.
Why aren't they out yet?

107
00:09:03.120 --> 00:09:04.440
Gosh. did someone die?

108
00:09:05.660 --> 00:09:06.770
Who are these two?

109
00:09:16.560 --> 00:09:17.470
You're here.

110
00:09:19.980 --> 00:09:21.840
A body found at night. and sure enough.

111
00:09:21.840 --> 00:09:23.810
you're on duty. Prosecutor Ju.

112
00:09:25.500 --> 00:09:26.680
Tell me about it.

113
00:09:28.360 --> 00:09:30.390
What were the circumstances
when the body was discovered?

114
00:09:30.390 --> 00:09:32.270
It was found by a drunk passerby.

115
00:09:32.540 --> 00:09:34.000
No external trauma at all.

116
00:09:35.390 --> 00:09:37.010
His nationality says Russian.

117
00:09:35.540 --> 00:09:37.030
[Aleksandr Kim]

118
00:09:37.050 --> 00:09:39.570
but as you can see.
he was likely a Koryoin.

119
00:09:39.960 --> 00:09:43.440
This guy had been in Korea
for less than a day.

120
00:09:43.710 --> 00:09:45.050
What's the cause of death?

121
00:09:45.050 --> 00:09:47.620
Cardiac arrest caused by drug poisoning.

122
00:09:51.030 --> 00:09:52.890
He's definitely a junkie.

123
00:09:53.130 --> 00:09:56.020
Suicide. drug addiction.
and death by violence;

124
00:09:56.260 --> 00:09:58.870
since this casino opened.
it's been a nightmare.

125
00:09:58.870 --> 00:10:00.020
Seriously.

126
00:10:02.260 --> 00:10:06.130
The latest trend for junkies
must be to inject into their necks.

127
00:10:06.730 --> 00:10:10.720
It's highly likely he got high
and accidentally stabbed his own neck.

128
00:10:11.050 --> 00:10:13.500
Anyway. he died of an overdose.

129
00:10:13.740 --> 00:10:16.740
Always the same old thing
with these casino visitors.

130
00:10:17.420 --> 00:10:18.950
Senior Assistant Lee Chaeha.

131
00:10:18.950 --> 00:10:19.780
Yes.

132
00:10:49.700 --> 00:10:51.120
It's a plastic fragment.

133
00:10:51.920 --> 00:10:52.920
And?

134
00:11:01.620 --> 00:11:02.410
Oh?

135
00:11:02.840 --> 00:11:05.060
I see some slight scratches.

136
00:11:06.180 --> 00:11:07.270
And?

137
00:11:08.300 --> 00:11:11.540
Do you think I called you here
for a treasure hunt?

138
00:11:11.870 --> 00:11:14.100
What you just did was mere observation.

139
00:11:14.340 --> 00:11:16.320
I want you to give me an analysis.

140
00:11:19.600 --> 00:11:21.130
This area is deserted.

141
00:11:21.410 --> 00:11:23.610
and there are no surveillance cameras.

142
00:11:28.190 --> 00:11:31.360
Could he have died
after injecting the drugs he bought here?

143
00:11:31.360 --> 00:11:33.900
He came all the way here from Russia
to get drugs? And...

144
00:11:33.900 --> 00:11:34.930
here. of all places?

145
00:11:34.930 --> 00:11:37.210
What if he didn't enter Korea
to buy drugs.

146
00:11:37.210 --> 00:11:39.230
but to sell them. and was then murdered?

147
00:11:39.230 --> 00:11:40.100
Based on what?

148
00:11:44.080 --> 00:11:47.170
An analysis without evidence
is just speculation. a mere opinion.

149
00:11:47.170 --> 00:11:48.880
I only want the truth.

150
00:11:49.200 --> 00:11:52.040
Yes. I'll start looking for it.

151
00:11:52.340 --> 00:11:53.800
I'm looking forward to it.

152
00:11:54.030 --> 00:11:54.780
Detective Ma.

153
00:11:54.780 --> 00:11:55.460
Yes.

154
00:11:55.970 --> 00:11:58.250
Please check the movement path
of the deceased.

155
00:11:58.250 --> 00:11:59.660
OK. got it.

156
00:12:01.090 --> 00:12:02.070
Hey.

157
00:12:02.270 --> 00:12:04.260
no pictures. please.

158
00:12:04.610 --> 00:12:06.140
You can't take pictures!

159
00:12:11.800 --> 00:12:13.320
Let's go eat.

160
00:12:14.370 --> 00:12:15.610
Oh. OK.

161
00:12:40.050 --> 00:12:42.780
Do you think it was
a natural or accidental death?

162
00:12:44.980 --> 00:12:47.800
From what we saw so far.
it looks like a drug overdose.

163
00:12:47.800 --> 00:12:49.680
What about
the scratches near his esophagus.

164
00:12:49.680 --> 00:12:51.280
and the needle mark on the neck?

165
00:12:51.280 --> 00:12:51.880
That's...

166
00:12:51.990 --> 00:12:54.000
And the plastic fragment
found in his mouth?

167
00:12:54.000 --> 00:12:55.110
That too...

168
00:12:57.150 --> 00:12:59.070
Let's talk again
after the final autopsy report

169
00:12:59.070 --> 00:13:00.100
is out.

170
00:13:00.350 --> 00:13:02.130
Submit today's duty report first.

171
00:13:02.130 --> 00:13:03.450
Yes. Prosecutor Ju.

172
00:13:06.860 --> 00:13:08.450
Corpses...

173
00:13:09.630 --> 00:13:10.890
don't seem to faze you.

174
00:13:12.380 --> 00:13:14.570
I came across them often when I was a cop.

175
00:13:14.570 --> 00:13:15.520
An ex-cop?

176
00:13:15.990 --> 00:13:17.030
Why did you quit?

177
00:13:17.960 --> 00:13:21.230
I couldn't adapt.
so I wanted to start over.

178
00:13:21.610 --> 00:13:22.640
What a shame.

179
00:13:23.000 --> 00:13:24.520
A National Police University graduate

180
00:13:24.520 --> 00:13:26.400
can swiftly become a superintendent.

181
00:13:26.400 --> 00:13:29.860
which is ranked higher
than a public official of Grade 5.

182
00:13:30.170 --> 00:13:31.580
It's fine.

183
00:13:31.810 --> 00:13:33.210
I don't think it's a pity.

184
00:13:34.470 --> 00:13:37.800
I didn't expect you to be so naive.

185
00:13:38.370 --> 00:13:39.250
What?

186
00:13:40.410 --> 00:13:43.540
It'll probably take you some time
to regret coming here.

187
00:13:45.730 --> 00:13:46.860
Are you done eating?

188
00:13:47.270 --> 00:13:48.730
Oh. yes.

189
00:14:04.020 --> 00:14:05.980
Um. Prosecutor Ju Taeseon.

190
00:14:06.690 --> 00:14:08.990
I'm glad to have worked with you today.

191
00:14:09.790 --> 00:14:12.760
Ever since I saw an article about you
when I was in university.

192
00:14:12.760 --> 00:14:14.560
I've respected you.

193
00:14:20.440 --> 00:14:23.710
I haven't done anything worthy of respect.

194
00:14:26.280 --> 00:14:28.690
I'm sorry if I made you uncomfortable.

195
00:14:29.710 --> 00:14:31.810
Why did you become a cop?

196
00:14:32.900 --> 00:14:33.610
I...

197
00:14:33.760 --> 00:14:35.460
I wanted to kill them

198
00:14:36.410 --> 00:14:38.210
whenever I saw them—murderers.

199
00:14:44.260 --> 00:14:48.160
Becoming a prosecutor
is the only way to legitimately

200
00:14:49.250 --> 00:14:50.470
kill murderers.

201
00:14:53.630 --> 00:14:55.800
Do exactly what you did during the crime!

202
00:14:55.800 --> 00:14:58.000
What are you waiting for? Get on with it!

203
00:15:04.460 --> 00:15:05.500
I didn't do it.

204
00:15:06.010 --> 00:15:07.390
I said I didn't do it!

205
00:15:07.690 --> 00:15:09.550
I didn't do it! Don't do this to me!

206
00:15:09.620 --> 00:15:11.240
I didn't do it!

207
00:15:11.660 --> 00:15:12.860
"I'm innocent."

208
00:15:13.470 --> 00:15:15.370
"I didn't do it."

209
00:15:15.870 --> 00:15:17.550
"My kid would never do such a thing."

210
00:15:17.550 --> 00:15:18.890
"It was an accident."

211
00:15:19.720 --> 00:15:20.990
Isn't it disgusting?

212
00:15:21.410 --> 00:15:23.690
They always say they're not at fault.

213
00:15:29.210 --> 00:15:30.250
You can get out.

214
00:15:30.520 --> 00:15:31.710
See you tomorrow.

215
00:15:53.000 --> 00:15:56.800
[To: Prosecutor Ju Taeseon]
[Thank you for all your hard work today]

216
00:15:58.030 --> 00:15:59.630
[To: Prosecutor Ju Taeseon]

217
00:16:08.060 --> 00:16:09.570
[Prosecution]

218
00:16:08.190 --> 00:16:09.210
Good morning.

219
00:16:15.860 --> 00:16:17.080
Good morning.

220
00:16:26.160 --> 00:16:27.430
Congrats. Chaeha.

221
00:16:28.730 --> 00:16:29.500
Sorry?

222
00:16:29.940 --> 00:16:31.560
A mere public official of Grade 8 like you

223
00:16:31.560 --> 00:16:34.960
bypassed all your seniors
to get the prosecutor's investigator job.

224
00:16:34.960 --> 00:16:38.090
Has anyone ever been transferred out
in just two months?

225
00:16:38.600 --> 00:16:40.330
Isn't this a promotion for you?

226
00:16:40.730 --> 00:16:42.850
I guess Prosecutor Ju
thinks highly of you.

227
00:16:42.850 --> 00:16:45.310
Didn't you two
do a shift together recently?

228
00:16:45.430 --> 00:16:46.720
Oh. yes.

229
00:16:46.980 --> 00:16:49.250
You two must have gotten along well
that night.

230
00:16:49.250 --> 00:16:52.290
Or maybe you have some secret weapon.

231
00:16:52.790 --> 00:16:55.760
Are you calling Chaeha a fox?

232
00:16:56.830 --> 00:16:57.900
Anyway. congrats.

233
00:17:06.020 --> 00:17:10.500
[Personnel Appointment: Grade 8 (Clerk)
Lee Chaeha. assigned as Investigator]

234
00:17:10.500 --> 00:17:14.700
[Room 512. Prosecutor's Office]
[Investigative support & case management]

235
00:17:14.700 --> 00:17:18.579
[Room 512. Criminal Division 1.
Danhyeon Office]

236
00:17:18.579 --> 00:17:22.310
[Prosecutor: Ju Taeseon]
[Investigator: Song Haneul] [Room 512]

237
00:17:25.310 --> 00:17:26.260
Come in.

238
00:17:36.000 --> 00:17:37.050
Prosecutor Ju.

239
00:17:37.270 --> 00:17:38.810
what is going on?

240
00:17:39.060 --> 00:17:39.990
What do you mean?

241
00:17:40.110 --> 00:17:41.970
I wasn't informed beforehand...

242
00:17:42.240 --> 00:17:44.330
People would kill for this position.

243
00:17:44.470 --> 00:17:46.670
Isn't this position out of your league?

244
00:17:47.030 --> 00:17:48.530
I never wanted it.

245
00:17:49.410 --> 00:17:51.070
Didn't you say you respect me?

246
00:17:51.860 --> 00:17:53.520
Do you not want to work with me.

247
00:17:54.140 --> 00:17:55.150
or

248
00:17:56.620 --> 00:17:59.550
do the murder cases I handle
make you uncomfortable?

249
00:17:59.710 --> 00:18:00.670
What?

250
00:18:03.140 --> 00:18:05.070
Of course you'd be uncomfortable.

251
00:18:05.470 --> 00:18:06.550
Lee Chaeha...

252
00:18:11.800 --> 00:18:12.780
you are

253
00:18:14.620 --> 00:18:15.510
the son

254
00:18:17.310 --> 00:18:18.360
of a...

255
00:18:20.720 --> 00:18:23.360
murderer. aren't you?

256
00:18:32.860 --> 00:18:34.930
[The Prosecutor's Proposal]

257
00:18:35.080 --> 00:18:36.090
Senior Assistant Lee Chaeha.

258
00:18:35.080 --> 00:18:38.650
[In the Next Episode]

259
00:18:37.450 --> 00:18:38.650
come work with me.

260
00:18:39.730 --> 00:18:41.590
Nice to meet you. I'm Song Haneul.

261
00:18:42.830 --> 00:18:43.830
You're here. sir!

262
00:18:45.840 --> 00:18:48.370
It seems that
the Koryoin. Kim. sold meth.

263
00:18:48.500 --> 00:18:51.050
You act as if
you've discovered something amazing.

264
00:18:51.050 --> 00:18:52.910
even trying to teach me what to do.

265
00:18:53.260 --> 00:18:54.220
You've got guts.

266
00:18:54.440 --> 00:18:55.840
I thought you'd run away.

267
00:19:00.150 --> 00:19:01.930
Do you dislike me?

268
00:19:02.140 --> 00:19:03.870
It seems you want me to like you.

269
00:19:03.950 --> 00:19:05.460
